== Infrastructure Due Diligence Analyst

=== Hierarchy Level
Entry-level to 3 years of experience, typically requiring degree in finance, engineering, economics, or related quantitative field

=== Key Activities and Responsibilities

*Financial Analysis & Modeling:*
- Building detailed discounted cash flow (DCF) models for infrastructure assets with 20-50 year cash flow projections
- Analyzing historical financial performance, revenue drivers, cost structures, and capital expenditure requirements
- Modeling regulatory frameworks and tariff reset methodologies (RAB models for regulated utilities)
- Conducting sensitivity analysis and scenario testing on key value drivers
- Assessing capital structure, debt serviceability, and refinancing risks
- Comparing valuation across different methodologies (DCF, precedent transactions, trading multiples)

*Commercial & Market Analysis:*
- Evaluating demand fundamentals and volume forecasts (traffic projections, energy demand, data center capacity)
- Analyzing competitive dynamics and market positioning
- Assessing contractual frameworks (concession agreements, power purchase agreements, offtake contracts)
- Understanding revenue mechanisms (availability payments, usage-based fees, merchant exposure)
- Reviewing customer composition, concentration risk, and contract duration/maturity profiles

*Due Diligence Coordination:*
- Managing due diligence data rooms and information requests
